Login form vailidation with server side :
#program save=serverform.php
<?php
#QueryString in php
include 'errorlipform.php';
?>
<html>
<head></head>
<body>
<?php validate();?>
<h1>Use Of Query String:</h1>
<form action="serverformvail.php?/=<?php echo basename($_SERVER['PHP_SELF']);?>" method="post">
  <p>
  Enter Your Email:<br/>
  <input type="text" name="email"/>
  <?php validate('email');?>
  </p>
  
  <p>
  Enter Your Password:<br/>
  <input type="password" name="password"/>
  <?php validate('password');?>
  </p>
  <input type="submit" name="btn" value="LOGIN"/>
</form>
</body>
</html>

#Program save=serverformvail.php
<?php
if($_SERVER['REQUEST_METHOD']=='POST')
{
	if(isset($_POST['btn']) and !empty($_POST['btn'])){
		
		$email=isset($_POST['email'])?$_POST['email']:NULL;
		$password=isset($_POST['password'])?$_POST['password']:NULL;
		if(is_null($email) or empty($email)){
			header("location:{$_REQUEST['/']}?action=email&msg=blank-email");
			
		}else if(is_null($password) or empty($password)){
			
			header("location:{$_REQUEST['/']}?action=password&msg=blank-password");
		}else{
			if($email=='ranjana@gmail.com' and $password=='123')
			{
				echo 'Welcome to the dashbord !';
			}else{
				header("location:{$_REQUEST['/']}?msg=login-faild");
			}
		}
	}else{
		header("location:{$_REQUEST['/']}?msg=invailid-btn");
	}
}else{
header("location:{$_REQUEST['/']}?msg=auth-failed");
}
	
?>

#Program save=errorlipform.php
<?php
$msg['auth-failed']="* You send a Illegal request !";
$msg['invailid-btn']="* Please Submit on the submit button !";
$msg['blank-email']="* Email can not be empty !";
$msg['blank-password']="* Password can not be empty !";
$msg['login-faild']="* Invailid email or password !";

function validate($action='')
{
	global $msg;
	$keyname=@$_REQUEST['msg'];
	$error=@$msg[$keyname];
	$request_action=@$_REQUEST['action'];
	    echo "<script>";
	echo "setTimeout(function(){
		document.getElementById('spn-error').style='display:none';
		
	},3000);";
	echo "</script>";

	if($action==$request_action and !empty($action))
	{
	   echo "<span style='color:red;'>{$error}</span>"	;
	   
	}
	if($action=='' and $request_action==NULL){
	   echo "<span style='color:red;'>{$error}</span>";
	}
}
?>
=============================================================================================
Redirection in PHP:php provides inbuilt function header("location:<url or target>") which can be 
used to redirect the user from one place to another place.

Example:
header("location:dashbord.php");

Maintaining the state in Query String:
You can use question mark(?) query String within header location to maintain state.

example:
header("location:dashbord.php?payment_id=1234567");
OR
header('location:dashbord.php?payment_id=1234567');
==================================================================
Redirection After few second:
header("refresh:time_delay_inseconds;url:path_of_page");

============
Js Scripting:
Since php is server side you can use php to generate Dynamic javascript or vice versa.


Js using php:
JS works on the basis script tag and you can use <script> tag that anywhere

==========
String Concatnation Operator:
dot(.) operator in php is used to concatenate String.
$name='ranjana';
$last="chaurasiya";
echo $name.$last;//output=ranjanachaurasiya
echo $name.' '.$last//output=ranjana chaurasiya
echo $name." ".$last//output=ranjana chaurasiya

$name=ranjana;
echo "<script>";
echo "var msg=' is good boy !';";
echo "window.alert(".'"'.$name.'"'." +msg);";//echo "window.alert(\"$name\"+msg);";
//echo "window.alert('$name'+msg);";
echo "</script>";

========================
How to redirect if JS code is used:
using Js function:
window.location.href="<any url name>";
=========
Note:When using window.location.href no print statement must be used.

